reviews.headline: No
reviews.comments: I found this foundation to be very heavy on my face and it didn't look natural. When I went into the Ulta store I told the greeter that I was looking for a foundation that wouldn't look like I was made up. This was not it. When I asked about another company's foundation she basically said it wasn't what I was looking for.

reviews.headline: MAC disappointed
reviews.comments: I have normal skin in hotter months and dry skin in cooler months. I purchased this during the winter. I wanted to like it bc its MAC but it made me super glowy as if I was sweating. Every time! Not my go to product for foundation.

reviews.headline: 2nd bottle
reviews.comments: That's my fav foundation ever, never changing it

reviews.headline: Worked well on my dry skin.
reviews.comments: Most foundations just go gross even with lotion and primer on my skin because of how dry it is. This seems to cover beautifully and has not left me with any patches.

reviews.headline: Just found my new favorite foundation!
reviews.comments:
The texture is silky and lightweight, yet it delivers amazing medium-to-full coverage without feeling heavy. My skin looks smooth, even, and radiant all day, no cakiness, no settling into fine lines.

The serum infusion makes such a difference it feels like I'm giving my skin a treatment while wearing makeup. It's hydrating but not greasy, and it wears beautifully for hours. I also love that the shade N40 matches my skin tone perfectly with no weird oxidation or patchiness.

If you're looking for a foundation that blends effortlessly, lasts all day, and leaves your skin looking like your best skin ever, this is it. Worth every penny!

reviews.headline: Yes it goes on smooth and moisturising.
reviews.comments: Goes on nice and smooth. Less coverage than the higher numbers bit still great.

reviews.headline: Love this product.
reviews.comments: It feels like the foundation and powder all-in-one.  It is smooth and it stays on all day for me.

reviews.headline: Awwesome
reviews.comments: It matches perfectly. Hope there is a waterproof form. Going on a cruise and I need waterproof everything we need to make sure.lol

reviews.headline: Light yet good coverage
reviews.comments: Have always used Mac, this was so light on the face, yet gave good coverage.  Did not feel like it was cakey.

reviews.headline: Obsessed, Extremely blurring
reviews.comments: My absolute favorite foundation mext to haus labs. This is so blurring on my skin, I recommend  using a gripping primer with this and i do wish that they had lighter shades. but seriously i would 100% recommend

reviews.headline: Great coverage with light feel
reviews.comments: Love this foundation - it's my only one!

reviews.headline: MAC never disappoints
reviews.comments: This is my all time favorite foundation. You can use a light hand with a sponge for a skin like look like i do, or you can build it up with a brush/more product. Either way it looks so nice snd glowy but not shiny. It lasts on my dry combo skin all day when i set with a tiny bit of powder and setting spray. I try so many different foundations and i keep coming back to this one.

reviews.headline: I would definitely buy again
reviews.comments: The serum foundation is a solid option for someone looking for coverage but not cakey coverage, which I've found with many of the other full-coverage foundations I've tried. It also feels nice on the skin, which makes sense with the serum component of the foundation. It is easy to apply with a damp sponge and lasts all day.

reviews.headline: Love it!!
reviews.comments: No foundation has ever worked well on my skin thats kinda oily but usually pretty dry. i prep my skin as always which is just with a light hydrating toner and use the elf hydra grip primer and it works so so good it lasts so long and looks so flawless, i live in a hot and humid area and it lasts so very good. never had a foundation like this. and the color match is perfect (i use NC11.5)

reviews.headline: I wanted to like itâ€¦.
reviews.comments:
Jealous of all the other people who experienced "dewy" skin cause that's not what I experienced at all! I would have to over apply to make it not look streaky or gross. It made my skin look so dry and gross. I only ended up trying this because the beauty blender skin tint was NOT sold at Ulta. Unfortunately, that product is now discontinued as well.

All in all, this wasn't for you. Looking at you Ulta employee ðŸ‘€ girl was like the only good stuff we have here is MAC

reviews.headline: I would buy it again
reviews.comments: Stays on pretty long

reviews.headline: Too dewy
reviews.comments: I usually use the now discontinued Studio Fix Formula and decided to give this one a try. This foundation was very dewy, it makes your skin look oily and shiny. Because it is so dewy the foundation moves as you apply bronzer and blush over it. I would not buy again.

reviews.headline: new go-to foundation!
reviews.comments: i have pretty dry skin and my undereyes normally crease pretty quickly, but i've had no issues with this foundation! the only little drawback i've found is it's hard to set with powder and the foundation ends up a little tacky. it doesn't accentuate my dry skin at all, though, which obviously i love. pretty similar to the tirtir cushion foundation, but is a little thicker.

reviews.headline: Too Dewy
reviews.comments: I bought this foundation a month ago because it was recommended by a worker in ulta. Although I told her I had oily skin she told me that it was good to use. It emphasized all my texture, made me more oily than usual and it is so bad in general because it visibly patches. I definitely DO NOT recommend this to anyone with oily skin

reviews.headline: Does NOT last.
reviews.comments: This foundation goes on well and looks pretty but does NOT last. I have normal (not dry or oily) skin and I put it on and an hour later I look like I'm sweating even if I set it with powder and setting spray. I just don't think it's worth the money as it doesn't work as advertised.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I'm excited to share my experience with this foundation, especially for people with extremely dry skin. As someone in the same boat, I've always struggled with foundations creating dry patches, but this one has turned out to be a game-changer. Mind you, I'm very picky with my foundation but the way it seamlessly melds with my skin without emphasizing dryness is truly impressive. 

My go to foundation is the Estee Lauder Future HydraLyst but trying this foundation will be my new favorite since it offers both better coverage (I have dark circles and hyperpigmentation) without being too shiny. I noticed sometimes that the EstÃ©e Lauder foundation wouldnt cover some of my hyper pigmentation so I would have to put on another layer or add concealer, which makes it slightly cakey (it also didn't oxidized). This one strikes the perfect balance. 

Living in the humid climate of Florida, I was initially skeptical about its staying power, but to my delight, it held up exceptionally well. Unlike other foundations that would slide off in the heat, this one remained  throughout the day. This will be apart of my everyday make up and even going out days!

For anyone with dry skin, I highly recommend giving this foundation a try. The hydration it provides, combined with its longevity, makes it an excellent choice. However, if you have oily skin, you might want to approach with caution as it could leave a slightly dewy finish that might not suit your preferences. Personally, I encountered no issues blending other makeup products on top and simply used a make up brush. I also had no breakout although I'm very acne prone. A suggestion is that I  wish it was water proof or had spf.

In conclusion, this foundation's ability to combat dryness, provide great coverage, and withstand hot and humid conditions makes it a winner for those of us with dry skin. It's a product I would highly recommend to anyone!!
faceoff_positive.headline: My new favorite foundation

faceoff_negative.comments:
I was very excited to receive and try this foundation from MAC and BzzAgent because the claim of it being like skin care, hydrating, and Moisturizing. As a person with dry skin at the moment, this was to drying and Matte for my tastes. When it's first applied, it's beautiful, radiant, and has a nice glow. As it wears throughout the day it becomes drying and clings to dry patches and in creases. After 1p hours of wear it was extremely cakey looking and has settled in my fine lines and creases. As a makeup artist I think this would work best for normal/Oily skin types and not dry/mature types that need hydration and like a radiant/glowy finish. 
I prepped my skin as usual for dry skin and didn't use setting powder only setting spray.
faceoff_negative.headline: Recommend for Normal/Oily skin types
